title: "Admin Subforums — Cuento Docs"
---

      <div class="docs-eyebrow">Admin Panel</div>
      <h1 class="docs-title">Subforums</h1>
      <p class="docs-lead">
        The Subforums page is where you build and maintain the structure of your board.
        Content is organised in a two-level hierarchy: <strong>Categories</strong> group
        related <strong>Subforums</strong> together. You can create, reorder, edit, and
        delete both from this page.
      </p>

      <div class="docs-screenshot">
        <img src="/assets/screenshots/admin-subforums.png" alt="Admin Subforums page screenshot" />
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Structure</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        Every subforum belongs to exactly one category. Categories provide top-level
        groupings (e.g. "In-Character", "Out-of-Character") while subforums are the
        actual boards where members post threads (e.g. "The Tavern", "Introductions").
      </p>

      <div class="callout">
        The page lists all categories in order, with each category's subforums
        nested beneath it. Scroll down to find the subforum you want to edit.
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Category fields</h2>

      <div class="field-list">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Name</div>
            <div class="field-values">text</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            The display name of the category, shown as a section heading on the forum index.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Position</div>
            <div class="field-values">number</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Controls the order in which categories appear. Lower numbers appear first.
            Categories with equal positions are sorted by their database ID.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Subforum fields</h2>

      <div class="field-list">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Name</div>
            <div class="field-values">text</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            The display name of the subforum, shown as a link on the forum index and in breadcrumbs.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Position</div>
            <div class="field-values">number</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Order of this subforum within its category. Lower numbers appear first.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Category ID</div>
            <div class="field-values">number</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            The ID of the parent category. Change this value to move the subforum to a
            different category. You can find a category's ID in its URL or by noting the
            order in which they appear on this page.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Description</div>
            <div class="field-values">rich text</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            A short description displayed below the subforum name on the forum index.
            The editor supports BBCode formatting — use the toolbar above the text area
            to add bold, italic, links, and other formatting.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Actions</h2>

      <div class="field-list">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Update</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Saves any changes made to that category or subforum's fields. Each item has
            its own Update button — clicking it saves only that item.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Delete</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Permanently removes the category or subforum. Deleting a category also removes
            all of its subforums. This cannot be undone — make sure you have moved any
            content you want to keep before deleting.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Creating new items</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        To add a new subforum or category, scroll to the bottom of the page and use
        the creation form. New items appear in the list immediately after you save them.
        Fill in all fields before saving — a subforum without a name or category ID
        cannot be saved.
      </p>
